      "text": "Diarrhea    Assessment:    Pt with continuous liquid diarrhea, slowed around 0100    Action:    Offered pt fecal incontinence bag, on bedpan as needed, am electrolytes    sent    Response:    Pt refused fecal incontinence bag at this time will continue to use    bedpan as needed, diarrhea slowing as noted above from 3x/hr at    beginning of shift to every couple of hours later on    Plan:    Continue to monitor, pt with GVHD, ongoing, pt on SS for electrolyte    repletion    Hypoxemia    Assessment:    Obtained pt on cool aerosol at 70% with FM, breath sounds with rhonchi    in upper lobes dim at bases, non-productive cough, pt denies SOB except    when laying on side, O2 sats 91-98%    Action:    Trending ABGs, titrating O2 as tolerated, 20mg IVP lasix given 0230, pt    being ruled out for TB, changed to negative pressure room and placed on    airborne precautions, induced sputum sent, AM cxray    Response:    Pt initially tolerating fiO2 of 50%, noted to be desating to low 90s    and then mid 80s around 0000, fiO2 increased to 70 and then 100% in    response, ABG obtained and pt placed on NRB, O2sats on NRB 95-98%,    lasix given as noted above    Plan:    Bronch today, f/u culture data, continue to trend ABGs, titrate    supplemental O2 as tolerated"
    }
